CFAO Motors, a subsidiary of the CFAO Group, has launched LOXEA by CFAO in Nigeria. A statement by the company said that LOXEA is present in 22 African countries, while it offers operating lease and fleet management solutions. The statement hinted that with this, its customers can have better access to the CFAO range of products like Mitsubishi and Suzuki cars, Fuso trucks, King Long buses, Toyota forklifts and JCB construction equipment. -Advertisement- Mr. Philippe Lefort, General Manager of LOXEA by CFAO, said that partnering with LOXEA would allow companies to enjoy the inherent benefits of the CFAO network, a trusted and reliable organisation that has been providing best-in-class products and services for over 119 years in the country. The statement explained that LOXEA offers a broad range of services from regular operating leases to comprehensive fleet management and car-sharing through a web portal and mobile applications through its three pillars; LOXEA Lease, LOXEA Connect, and LOXEA Ride. LOXEA Lease provides rental of vehicles or equipment from 36 to 48 months with full maintenance according to the manufacturer’s prescription, full comprehensive insurance, replacement vehicle (after 48 hours), and geolocation. The fleet management solution provides a fleet manager, Drivers 24/7, fuel card management, fleet analytics, and fleet mobility optimisation. The company emphasised that through the LOXEA Connect application, customers can have access to real-time monitoring of fleet usage and behaviour. POLL Lefort added: “Our goal is to establish and maintain long-term business relationships by adding value to businesses who outsource their vehicle management by ensuring their fleet is operational 24/7.”